==Romanian==
===Etymology===
Substratum word, akin to (or borrowed by) Albanian ''[[ylber]]''
Note:
Might be a compound of *''curcu'' from Latin ''[[circus]]'' and *''beu''. Compare Italian ''[[arcobaleno]]'', Sardinian ''circuvoglia'' (*circu-vrongia), Sardinian (Logudorese) ''arcu de chelu'' and ''arcubaradu'', Sicilian ''arcubbalenu'' and Romagnolo ''arcobalèin''. 

[[Category:Romance etymology]]
see: www.geocities.com/protoillyrian for more information

